{{Han etyl}}

{{Han compound|螾|t1=earthworm|日|t2=sun/day|ls=psc}}.

The pictographic protoform of [[螾]] was borrowed to represent "period of days" in oracle bone script. In bronze inscriptions, the semantic component [[日]] (“sun/day”) was added to this character. The phonetic component was mixed with another common semantic component [[勹]] ("bow down") in Warring States period, hence the incorrect analysis in ''{{w|Shuowen Jiezi}}'' of this character as {{Han compound|勹|日}}.
